OL,3,CHegseth makes D-Day speech about
OL,4,C'dangerous ideologies' invading Europe
OL,6,FWhile the exact number of German
OL,7,Fcasualties is unknown, historians
OL,8,Festimate between 4,000 and 9,000 men
OL,9,Fwere killed, wounded or missing. On
OL,10,Fthe Allied front, a total of 4,414
OL,11,Fdied.
OL,13,FThe Battle of Normandy, which followed
OL,14,Fthe landings, saw 73,000 Allied lives
OL,15,Flost with 153,000 men wounded.
OL,17,FCommemorations also took place at the
OL,18,FBritish Normandy Memorial, and across
OL,19,FJuno Beach.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
